[SN]TITLE[SN]
Glasgow duo Henry Pyrgos and Fraser Brown undergo surgery

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Scrum-half Henry Pyrgos has been ruled out for about four months after having surgery on a wrist that he damaged while on World Cup duty with Scotland.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
His Glasgow Warriors and international team-mate Fraser Brown is expected to be missing for around eight weeks.
The 26-year-old hooker has had an operation on a foot injury.
Warriors head coach Gregor Townsend said: "We wish Henry and Fraser all the best with their rehab and we look forward to welcoming them back."
